Especially on 32-bit Solaris, but also occasionally 32-bit Linux, mock server tests seem to lock up and timeout. Characteristic errors are like:
{code}
mock_server_replies(): precondition failed: request
{code}
... which indicates that the mock server waited over 10 seconds to receive or process a message from the driver.

I propose disabling mock server tests on 32-bit, I suspect the bug is in the mock server, not the driver.

